<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FF84FFDE6DC2FA05FC72AEEA" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF84FFDE6DC2FA05FC72AEEA" blockId="32.[178,1085,1432,1512]" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545">
Diagnosis: Four elytral carinae are very prominent on the elytral disc of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF84FFDE6DC2FA28FE32AEC8" authority="CHEVROLAT, 1834" authorityName="CHEVROLAT" authorityYear="1834" box="[178,423,1461,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyciformis">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF84FFDE6DC2FA28FE32AEC8" box="[178,423,1461,1482]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545">Platynoptera lyciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF84FFDE6C94FA2BFDF5AEC8" authority="(KLUG)" box="[484,608,1461,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampliata">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF84FFDE6C94FA2BFE66AEC9" box="[484,499,1462,1483]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF84FFDE6F76FA28FDF5AEC8" box="[518,608,1461,1482]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545">ampliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But, specimens of 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF84FFDE6E4FFA28FC31AEC8" box="[831,932,1461,1482]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545">lyciformis</emphasis>
have a broad testaceous fascia on the elytral disc, which is not the case in 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF84FFDE6E66FA4FFCE5AEE5" box="[790,880,1490,1511]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="1545">ampliata</emphasis>
specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
